New Records: Travis Head scored a career-best 154 not out, the highest individual score by an Australian in England
Key Match Events: Australia successfully chased down 316 to win the match by seven wickets, with six overs remaining
England's innings ended with nine wickets for 315 all out
Pre-Game Insights: England scored 315 all out after being 211-2 after 32 overs
Australia relied on spinners, including part-time bowler Marnus Labuschagne, to control the run rate
Post-Match Reflections: Travis Head celebrated his century by raising his helmet to the sky
Australia's captain Mitchell Marsh praised the team's performance and the effectiveness of their spinners
Miscellaneous Highlights: Ben Dwarshuis made his ODI debut but sustained a pectoral strain and was unable to return
The match was played at Trent Bridge, known for its short boundaries
